Write a program to readd2 integer values 'a' and 'b'. Perform the following bitwise operations between a and b and store the
results in new variables: |, &,^,>>,<<. Also perform unitary operations on a: You can validate the results by using pen and paper
to convert decimals into binary and matchng results.

#include <stdio.h>
int main() 
{
    int a=2, b=3;
    
    int andResult = a & b;
    int xorResult = a ^ b;
    int leftShiftResult = a << b;
    int rightShiftResult = a >> b;
    int orResult = a|b;

    printf("Bitwise AND result: %d\n", andResult);
    printf("Bitwise XOR result: %d\n", xorResult);
    printf("Left shift result: %d\n", leftShiftResult);
    printf("Right shift result: %d\n", rightShiftResult);
    printf("Bitwise OR result: %d\n", orResult);

    return 0;
}
